Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-001
This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshot can open
<dl>    
    <dt>Open xfce4 screenshot</dt>
        <dd>The Screenshot window opens</dd>
</dl>

Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-002
This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshot saves a screenshot of the whole screen as you see it
<dl>
    <dt>Open Screenshot</dt>
        <dd>The take a screenshot window should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>Select the "Entire screen" option, under the 'Region to capture' section and click the OK button</dt>
        <dd>The screenshot action window should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>Select the "Save" option, under the 'Action' section and click the ok button</dt>
        <dd>A save dialog should be displayed, allowing to set the save location and the name of the file</dd>
</dl>

Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-003
This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshot copies a screenshot to the clipboard
<dl>
    <dt>Open Screenshot</dt>
        <dd>The take a screenshot window should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>Select the "Entire screen" option, under the 'Region to capture' section and click the OK button</dt>
        <dd>The screenshot action window should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>Select the "Copy to the clipboard" option, under the 'Action' section and click the OK button</dt>
        <dd>The screenshot should be copied to the clipboard, allowing it to be pasted in another application</dd>
</dl>

Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-004
This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshot opens a copy of a screenshot with another application
<dl>
    <dt>Open Screenshot</dt>
        <dd>The take a screenshot window should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>Select the "Entire screen" option, under the 'Region to capture' section and click the OK button</dt>
        <dd>The screenshot action window should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>Select the "Open with:" option, under the 'Action' section</dt>
        <dd>The drop-down list box should now be enabled and clickable</dd>
    <dt>Click on the drop-down list</dt>
        <dd>A list of available applications should drop down</dd>
    <dt>Select one of the available applications and click the OK button</dt>
        <dd>The screenshot should be saved to the system's temporary directory and opened with the application chosen from the drop-down list</dd>
</dl>

Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-005
This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshot allows to host a copy of a screenshot on a free online hosting service
<dl>
    <dt>Open Screenshot</dt>
        <dd>The take a screenshot window should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>Select the "Entire screen" option, under the 'Region to capture' section and click the OK button</dt>
        <dd>The screenshot action window should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>Select the "Host on ZimageZ" option, under the 'Action' section and click the OK button</dt>
        <dd>ZimageZ dialog window should open</dd>
    <dt>Fill all the fields of ZimageZ dialog window and click the OK button</dt>
        <dd>The screenshot should be hosted on this free online hosting service, and easily shareable with other people</dd>
</dl>

Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-006
This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshot saves a screenshot of the active window
<dl>
    <dt>Open Screenshot</dt>
        <dd>The take a screenshot window should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>Select the "Active window" option, under the 'Region to capture' section and click the OK button</dt>
        <dd>The screenshot action window should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>Select the "Save" option, under the 'Action' section and click the ok button</dt>
        <dd>A save dialog should be displayed, allowing to set the save location and the name of the file</dd>
</dl>

Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-007
This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshot saves a screenshot by clicking and dragging a rectangle over a area of the screen, before releasing the mouse button
<dl>
    <dt>Open Screenshot</dt>
        <dd>The take a screenshot window should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>Select the "Select a region" option, under the 'Region to capture' section and click the OK button</dt>
        <dd>The screen should darken</dd>
    <dt>Click the left mouse button and drag a rectangle over a area of the screen, before releasing the mouse button</dt>
        <dd>The screenshot action window should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>Select the "Save" option, under the 'Action' section and click the ok button</dt>
        <dd>A save dialog should be displayed, allowing to set the save location and the name of the file</dd>
</dl>

Test-case name: xfce4 screenshooter/xfce4-screenshooter-008
This test will check that Xfce4 Screenshot allows to select whether or not the screenshot will include the mouse pointer
<dl>
    <dt>Open Screenshot</dt>
        <dd>The take a screenshot window should be displayed</dd>
    <dt>Select one of the options, under the 'Region to capture', tick the "Capture the mouse pointer" option section</dt>
    <dt>Point the mouse pointer to the textbox's top arrow button, under the 'Delay before capturing'</dt>
        <dd>The number of seconds should increase accordingly</dd>
    <dt>Select one of the options, under the 'Region to capture' and click the OK button</dt>
        <dd>The screenshot active window should only be displayed after the number of established seconds has elapsed</dd>
        <dd>The saved screenshot should include the mouse pointer</dd>
</dl>

<strong>If all actions produce the expected results listed, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> a 'passed' result.
    If an action fails, or produces an unexpected result, please <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> 'failed' and <a href="../../buginstructions">file a bug</a>. Please be sure to include the bug number when you <a href="results#add_result">submit</a> your result</strong>
